<title>USA: Novartis Corp gets U.S. corn-protection patent.</title>
<headline>Novartis Corp gets U.S. corn-protection patent.</headline>
<dateline>GOLDEN ALLEY, Minn. 1997-01-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Novartis Corp said it received a U.S. patent covering the control of insect larvae in corn plants, and also filed suit against several other U.S. seed and agricultural companies.</p>
<p>Novartis said its patent covers a method of protecting corn against insects, including the European corn borer.</p>
<p>In a statement issued Tuesday, Novartis said it filed patent infringement lawsuits against Monsanto Co, DeKalb Genetics Corp, and Pioneer Hi-Bred International Inc.</p>
<p>Novartis, an affiliate of Novartis AG of Switzerland, produces and sells corn, soybean, alfalfa, sunflower, sorghum, sugarbeet, vegetable and flower seeds.</p>
<p>((Reuters Chicago Newsdesk (312) 408-8787))</p>
